642	\section{Mayer-Vietoris LES short-complex infrastructure (iter-019)}
643	\label{sec:hmodule_prime_mayer_vietoris_short_complex}
644	
645	Iter-019 lays the carrier of the eventual $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$-flavored short exact sequence on which the connecting hom $\delta$ of the Mayer-Vietoris LES is built. The short complex is a direct mirror of Mathlib's $\AddCommGrpCat$-flavored \lstinline{MayerVietorisSquare.shortComplex} (\texttt{MayerVietorisSquare.lean} L234--249), with $\AddCommGrpCat.\free$ replaced by $\ModuleCat.\free\,k$. The infrastructure decomposes into three declarations: a one-line Mathlib gap-fill instance, a pushout-of-free-sheaves analog (lemma), and the short-complex carrier (definition).
646	
647	\subsection{Mathlib gap and the helper instance}
648	
649	Mathlib registers $(\AddCommGrpCat.\free).\IsLeftAdjoint$ in \lstinline{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/Grp/Adjunctions.lean} L84 as a typeclass instance, enabling $\Sheaf.\composeAndSheafify\,J\,\AddCommGrpCat.\free$ to acquire the necessary $\PreservesColimit$ instance. Mathlib's \lstinline{ModuleCat/Adjunctions.lean} provides the adjunction \lstinline{ModuleCat.adj k : ModuleCat.free k ⊣ forget (ModuleCat k)} but does not register the corresponding $\IsLeftAdjoint$ instance (that registration lives only in \lstinline{ModuleCat/Topology/Basic.lean} for topological modules, an unrelated context). This is a real Mathlib gap on the path to a $\ModuleCat\,k$-flavored Mayer-Vietoris LES.
650	
651	The iter-019 helper fills the gap with a one-line instance:
652	
653	\begin{definition}[Helper instance: $\ModuleCat.\free\,k$ is left adjoint (iter-019)]
654	  \label{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_isLeftAdjoint}
655	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.ModuleCat_free_isLeftAdjoint}
656	  \uses{}
657	  Let $k : \mathrm{Type}\,u$ be a field. Then $\ModuleCat.\free\,k$ is a left adjoint:
658	  \[
659	    (\ModuleCat.\free\,k).\IsLeftAdjoint \;:=\; \langle \_, \langle \ModuleCat.\mathtt{adj}\,k \rangle\rangle.
660	  \]
661	\end{definition}
662	
663	\begin{proof}
664	  \uses{}
665	  The body is a structural term-mode value packaging Mathlib's existing \lstinline{ModuleCat.adj k : ModuleCat.free k ⊣ forget (ModuleCat k)} into the typeclass-witness form expected by \lstinline{Functor.IsLeftAdjoint}. No proof tactics; just typeclass registration. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-019) confirms the full block typechecks end-to-end against current Mathlib + post-iter-018 project state, kernel-only axioms.
666	\end{proof}
