668	\subsection{The pushout-of-free-sheaves analog}
669	
670	\begin{lemma}[Pushout of free $\ModuleCat\,k$-sheaves under a Mayer-Vietoris square (iter-019)]
671	  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_isPushoutModuleCatFreeSheaf}
672	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_isPushoutModuleCatFreeSheaf}
673	  \uses{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_isLeftAdjoint}
674	  Let $k$ be a field, $C$ a category with $J : \mathrm{GrothendieckTopology}\,C$, and assume $\HasWeakSheafify\,J\,(\mathrm{Type}\,u)$ and $\HasSheafify\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$. Let $S : J.\MayerVietorisSquare$. Then the image of $S$ under the composite
675	  \[
676	    \yoneda \;\circ\; \Functor.\whiskeringRight\,(\ModuleCat.\free\,k) \;\circ\; \presheafToSheaf\,J\,\_
677	  \]
678	  is a pushout square in $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$.
679	\end{lemma}
680	
681	\begin{proof}
682	  \uses{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_isLeftAdjoint}
683	  Direct mirror of Mathlib's $\mathtt{GrothendieckTopology.MayerVietorisSquare.isPushoutAddCommGrpFreeSheaf}$ (\texttt{MayerVietorisSquare.lean} L154--160) with $\AddCommGrpCat.\free \rightarrow \ModuleCat.\free\,k$. The proof reads as: (1) start with $S.\isPushout$, the type-level pushout; (2) push it through $\Sheaf.\composeAndSheafify\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\free\,k)$ (which preserves pushouts because $\ModuleCat.\free\,k$ is a left adjoint, registered by Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_isLeftAdjoint}); (3) translate the resulting square's shape via the canonical iso $\presheafToSheaf\composeAndSheafify\mathrm{Iso}$ between two ways of writing $\presheafToSheaf\,J\,\_ \circ (\yoneda \circ \mathrm{whiskerRight}\,\free)$. Body:
684	  \begin{lstlisting}
685	  (S.isPushout.map (Sheaf.composeAndSheafify J (ModuleCat.free k))).of_iso
686	    ((Square.mapFunctor.mapIso
687	      (presheafToSheafCompComposeAndSheafifyIso J (ModuleCat.free k))).app
688	        (S.map yoneda))
689	  \end{lstlisting}
690	  Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-019) confirms the body typechecks end-to-end against current Mathlib + post-iter-018 project state, kernel-only axioms (\lstinline{propext}, \lstinline{Classical.choice}, \lstinline{Quot.sound}). Every component (\lstinline{Sheaf.composeAndSheafify}, \lstinline{Square.IsPushout.map}, \lstinline{Square.IsPushout.of_iso}, \lstinline{presheafToSheafCompComposeAndSheafifyIso}, \lstinline{Square.mapFunctor.mapIso}) is value-category-agnostic in Mathlib; the proof transfers cleanly.
691	\end{proof}
