720	\begin{remark}[Why this is the natural iter-019 step]
721	  Mathlib's connecting hom $\delta$ for the Mayer-Vietoris LES (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L112--114) reads
722	  \[
723	    \delta \;:=\; \mathtt{AddCommGrpCat.ofHom}\,(S.\mathtt{shortComplex\_shortExact}.\mathtt{extClass}.\mathtt{precomp}\,\_\,(\mathtt{by\ omega})),
724	  \]
725	  which uses $S.\mathtt{shortComplex\_shortExact}$ — a $\Sheaf\,J\,\AddCommGrpCat$-valued short exact sequence (Mathlib L267--268). To obtain a $\ModuleCat\,k$-flavored $\delta$, we need the analog $S.\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{shortComplex\_shortExact}$ in $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$. This decomposes naturally into:
726	  \begin{enumerate}
727	    \item \textbf{Iter-019:} the carrier $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex$ + the underlying pushout lemma + the helper instance (this section).
728	    \item \textbf{Iter-020+:} $\mathtt{Mono}\,\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.f$, $\mathtt{Epi}\,\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.g$, $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.\mathtt{Exact}$ instance derivations (mirror Mathlib L252--265, ~10--15 LOC).
729	    \item \textbf{Iter-021:} the named lemma $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\_\mathtt{shortExact}$ packaging the above into a $\mathtt{ShortExact}$ structure (mirror Mathlib L267--268, ~3 LOC).
730	    \item \textbf{Iter-022+:} the connecting hom $\HModulePrime\_\delta$ via $\mathtt{ModuleCat.ofHom}\,(\mathtt{shortComplex\_shortExact}.\mathtt{extClass}.\mathtt{precomp})$.
